{
  "texts": [
    "The sensitivity computation for the weight update is obtained using the adjoint state method [453,527], as backpropagating through each time step of the solver leads to a high memory cost.",
    "This also makes it possible to treat the solver as a black box.",
    "Similar extensions to PDEs [525] have been proposed by considering recurrent CNNs with residual connections, where the CNNs act as spatial gradients.Similarly, [528] establish a connection between deep residual RNNs and iterative solvers.",
    "Residual connections in NNs allow information to bypass NN layers.",
    "Consider the estimation of the next state of a PDE with a classical solveru t+1 = u(t + t) = F[u(t)]."
  ]
}